HEADWORD: Subindividual
<hw>Sub*in`di*vid"u*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A division
of that which is individual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An individual can not branch itself into
<qex>subindividuals</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subinduce</ent>⟦br⟧
